randoop
Class ObjectCheck

Object
  ObjectCheck
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable, Check
public class ObjectCheck
extends Object
implements Check

A check that checks for expected properties of one or more values generated during the execution of a Sequence, for example:

  • Checking that the objects created during execution of a sequence respect reflexivity, transitivity and symmetry of equality
  • Checking that calling toString() on the objects created during execution of a sequence does not throw an exception.

Randoop performs these checks after a statement in a sequence is executed and has resulted in possibly new or modified objects;

An ObjectCheck has two parts:

  • A ObjectContract object, that is responsible for performing the actual check on a set of runtime values. For example. the class EqualsReflexive is a checker code class that, given an object o, calls o.equals(o) and checks whether it returns true.
  • A list of s, which describe the specific values in a sequence that the check is over; Property objects do not deal with these details.
